cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a novel distributed framework for detecting risk SNPs for Alzheimer's disease across multiple research institutions, which involves machine learning techniques such as model selection and feature selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves privacy-preserving techniques, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper deals with genetic data, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
